| Paper                                               | Core Idea                                                                                 | Control Philosophy                 |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| **Stability and Control Despite Rotor Loss (2014)** | Accept the unavoidable spin and control the reduced attitude.                             | **Classical Control (LQR)**        |
| **Uniform Passive FTC**                             | Treat rotor failures as disturbances and use a single controller without fault detection. | **Passive Fault-Tolerant Control** |
| **Nonlinear MPC for FTC**                           | Predict future states and compute optimal control inputs subject to constraints.          | **Optimization-Based Control**     |
